\title{causatr: Unified Causal Effect Estimation for Methodological Triangulation}
\description{
Estimates causal effects via g-computation, inverse probability weighting, and matching for methodological triangulation. Primary engine is the parametric g-formula and iterated conditional expectation (ICE) g-computation with empirical sandwich variance estimation. Ships a self-contained density-ratio IPW engine and delegates matching to MatchIt. Supports binary, continuous, categorical, and multivariate treatments (multivariate is g-computation only); static, dynamic, modified treatment, and stochastic interventions (stochastic is g-computation only); continuous, binary, count (Poisson, negative binomial), quasibinomial (fractional), Gamma, and beta regression outcomes; and external observation weights. Longitudinal data is handled via ICE g-computation. Cluster-robust variance beyond matching subclasses is planned.
}
